so here is the responses when you fetch or get stations, routes, trips, fares and some others, so looking at them now you can work on the home page where you update the stations to use the live api data and then falllback to mock data if not available. the data will increase in size and if we put everything in one request the api returns about 3mb upwards so the backend will be strutured to be paginated that is you get a limited number of iems at a lower sixze then the rest you query next pages to get them. for now the endpoint is not working like that so try to get the response frm the normal url but also have the pagination in place so when its ready it will kick in

curl -X 'GET' \
  'https://api.trotro.live/api/trips/' \
  -H 'accept: application/json' \
  -H 'X-CSRFTOKEN: VJDERMm2s5GzgeH54GTth5n88QTWTYZq4sXhJMjTuQ11cfyJev0woLOanHDckh5G'
